description: MADRID – Iranian director Jafar Panahi recently added another international accolade to his name by winning the Palme d’Or at the Cannes Film Festival with It Was Just an Accident.
title: Self-orientalization of Iranian cinema: the mirror the west wants to see

description: TEHRAN – The U.S.-Israel relationship has long been a pillar of American foreign policy in West Asia, influencing security dynamics and shaping economic alliances. While their military and economic partnership remains robust, recent events—particularly the Israeli war on Gaza and Iran’s peaceful nuclear program—have reignited questions about the true nature of their ties.
title: Theatrical performance or genuine divide? U.S.-Israel approach in West Asia

description: TEHRAN – Western states have long used the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) as a tool of pressure against Iran, recycling discredited Israeli intelligence and crying "non-compliance" whenever diplomatic progress fails to yield them concessions from Iran.  But after years of this tired strategy - and despite Iranians’ continued good-faith cooperation - Tehran may finally be ready to reset the equation.
title: IAEA’s old playbook may lead to different consequences this time

description: TEHRAN – Concurrent with the “Picasso in Tehran” exhibition, which is underway at the Tehran Museum of Contemporary Art (TMoCA), the 2012 Spanish movie “Picasso's Gang” directed by Fernando Colomo was screened at the cinematheque of the museum on Sunday.
title: TMoCA screens Fernando Colomo’s “Picasso's Gang”

description: TEHRAN – “The Thin Man” by American writer Samuel Dashiell Hammett has been published in Persian by Now Publications in Tehran.
title: “The Thin Man” at Iranian bookstores

description: TEHRAN- The Iran National Music Orchestra will perform a concert titled "Remaining with a Gaze" in tribute to the late composer and conductor Homayoun Khorram.
title: Iran National Orchestra to perform in memory of Homayoun Khorram

description: TEHRAN – For the first time in Iran, a special concert of music from the Harry Potter films was held at the Espinas Palace Hotel in Tehran on Saturday night, with more than 6,000 people in attendance in two performances.
title: Harry Potter film concert in Tehran extended for two more performances

description: TEHRAN— A subtle yet pervasive campaign jeopardizing the foundation of free speech and democratic dissent has emerged in the shadow of America's political theater. Project Esther is more than just a policy initiative. It was designed by the Heritage Foundation and is now part of the Trump administration's second term.
title: Project Esther: Trump’s blueprint to crush Palestine advocacy

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Deputy Foreign Minister for Legal and International Affairs, Kazem Gharibabadi, has issued a stern rebuke of a recent International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) report on Iran’s nuclear activities, describing it as a politically motivated document reliant on “fabricated data” from the Israeli regime.
title: Iran warns IAEA not to test its patience after watchdog’s politically charged report

description: TEHRAN – Speaker of Iran’s parliament Mohammad Bagher Qalibaf arrived in Caracas on Sunday, leading a high-level parliamentary delegation.
title: Iran parliament speaker begins strategic Latin America tour with official visit to Venezuela

description: TEHRAN – The Israeli occupation regime kills and injures scores of starving civilians at a “failed” U.S. aid distribution center.
title: Massacre at Gaza starvation camp

description: BEIRUT — Israel’s Channel 14 reported on Sunday that Morgan Ortagus, Deputy Special Presidential Envoy for West Asia, would soon leave her post. The news channel said this move “is not good news as Ortagus was a strong supporter of Israel and worked decisively on the issue of disarming Hezbollah.”
title: Ortagus’s successor, another ugly face of Washington

description: TEHRAN - Etemad examined a possible nuclear agreement between Iran and the United States and the obstacles ahead in an interview with reformist political activist Ali Bagheri.
title: Agreement is within reach

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi left Tehran Sunday evening to begin a two-day diplomatic mission to Egypt and Lebanon, where he is expected to hold high-level meetings, according to Foreign Ministry Spokesman Esmaeil Baghaei.
title: Araghchi to pursue diplomatic coordination on Gaza in visits to Egypt, Lebanon

description: TEHRAN – In a ceremony held on Sunday, Brigadier General Kioumars Heidari, Commander of the Iranian Army Ground Forces, announced the deployment of 21 Iranian military officers to international peacekeeping missions in four African nations—Eritrea, Ethiopia, Sudan, and Mali.
title: 21 officers deployed to peace missions in Africa: Iran top commander

description: Several drones targeted a military installation in Irkutsk Region on Sunday in what authorities say is the first such attack in Siberia. Governor Igor Kobzev confirmed the strike and said the incident occurred near the settlement of Sredny, about 150 km from Lake Baikal and 70 km from the eponymous regional capital.
title: First drone attack reported in Siberia

description: Iraqi Prime Minister Mohammed Shia al-Sudani and visiting Lebanese President Joseph Aoun on Sunday called for an immediate intervention to “save the people of Gaza” and denounced the continued Israeli assault on the enclave amid “suspicious international silence”.
title: Iraq, Lebanon leaders call for urgent intervention to ‘save the people of Gaza’

description: The Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine (PFLP) has condemned “the new massacre of the starving people in Rafah”, in which at least 30 people were killed when Israeli forces opened fire on Palestinians approaching a U.S.-backed aid point, saying it was “a genocide with international complicity and American participation”.
title: Israel committed ‘full-fledged war crime’ by killing aid seekers: PFLP

description: Bassam Zaqout, director of the Palestinian Medical Relief Society, has described the chaotic scenes at aid distribution points following the deadly Israeli attack in Rafah.
title: Israeli soldiers open fire when crowds grow at aid points: Charity chief

description: Prince Faisal bin Farhan Al Saud, the Saudi foreign minister, says the Israeli government’s refusal to allow a delegation of Arab ministers to the occupied West Bank showed its “extremism and rejection of peace”, Al Jazeera reported.
title: Saudi FM says Israel blocking Ramallah meeting proof of ‘extremism’

description: A Palestinian father who had lost nine of his 10 children in an Israeli airstrike has died from wounds sustained in the same attack, local health officials have said.
title: Gaza doctor who lost nine children in Israeli airstrike dies from wounds

description: TEHRAN – Persepolis football club completed the signing of Mohammadhossein Sadeghi on Sunday.
title: Persepolis complete signing of Mohammadhossein Sadeghi

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s women’s hockey defeated India 5-1 in the 2025 IIHF Women's Asia Cup on Sunday.
title: Iran victorious over India in 2025 IIHF Women's Asia Cup

description: TEHRAN – Iran national football team head coach Amir Ghalenoei announced his 28-man team for two matches against Qatar and North Korea in the 2026 World Cup qualification.
title: Iran squad for FIFA World Cup 2026 qualifiers against Qatar, North Korea

description: TEHRAN – Known for its natural beauty and tranquil surroundings, Lahijan Lake, is a gem in the heart of Iran’s northern region, famed for its tea plantations and lush greenery.
title: Lahijan Lake, shining gem in northern Iran

description: TEHRAN--Eskelim waterfall, which is also known as Galesh Kola waterfall, is located in the heart of the dense forests of Savadkuh in Mazandaran province. This waterfall, with a height of about 30 meters and a width of 10 meters, is made of limestone and has healing properties due to the mineral salts in the water.
title: Eskelim waterfall, a gem in the heart of Savadkuh forests

description: TEHRAN--With the global registration of Yazd’s traditional goldsmithing art by UNESCO, this desert city is emerging as a unique destination for tourism, where gold, heritage, and desert landscapes offer visitors a unique experience.
title: Iran desert gold tourism flourishes after UNESCO recognition

description: TEHRAN—Managing Director of Ali Sadr Travel Company Mehran Hajian donated a symbolic gift to South Korean Ambassador in Iran Kim Junpyo following his visit from Ali Sadr Cave in Hamedan province. With donation of exquisite pottery made by Lalejin artisans to South Korean ambassador, Hajian said, “This precious gift is the result of the taste and skill of Lalejini pottery artisans. It is a symbol of ancient heritage, cultural identity and handicrafts of Hamedan people,” Miras Arya (CHTN) reported.
title: Lalejin pottery donated to South Korean ambassador

description: TEHRAN--The spokesperson for the Islamic City Council of Isfahan said: The Isfahan City Council supports the suspension of Barcelona's cooperation with Tel Aviv.
title: Isfahan City Council supports suspension of Barcelona's cooperation with Tel Aviv

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s women’s football team will face Iraq in two friendly matches in Tehran.
title: Iran’s women’s football team to play two friendlies against Iraq

description: TEHRAN – The health ministry is planning to start the Family Physician Program in cities and villages with a population of less than 20,000 individuals on June 22, the first day of spring.
title: Family Physician Program to kick off in mid-June

description: TEHRAN – Launched by the United Nations Children’s Fund (UNICEF) and the Ministry of Sport and Youth, TORANJ Adolescent and Youth Empowerment Program aims to support adolescent and young people, focusing on skills development, education, and life readiness.
title: TORANJ program to promote adolescent, youth well-being

description: TEHRAN- Spokesman for Majlis (the Iranian Parliament)'s presiding board announced the government's introduction of the proposed economy minister to this board on Sunday.
title: Seyed Ali Madanizadeh proposed as new economy minister

description: TEHRAN – The Information and Communication Technology (ICT) Minister, Sattar Hashemi, has chaired a specialized session on Sustainable Digital Infrastructure and Accessibility at the Asia-Pacific Telecommunity Ministerial Meeting (APT-MM), held in Japan.
title: Iran chairs Asia-Pacific Telecommunity Ministerial Meeting

description: TEHRAN – Venezuela has received a total of 2.4 million doses of Iranian-made vaccines, including 1.905 million doses of polio vaccine and 502,000 doses of hepatitis B vaccine.
title: Venezuela receives 2.4m doses of Iranian-made polio, hepatitis B vaccines

description: TEHRAN- Amirabad Port Complex, also referred to locally as Imam Khomeini Port, is a principal maritime gateway in northern Iran.
title: Amirabad port complex: Iran’s northern gateway to Eurasia

description: TEHRAN- Abdolamir Rabihavi, the director general for West Asia at Iran’s Trade Promotion Organization (TPO), referred to the details of trade documents and agreements recently signed between Iran and Oman, and mentioned preferential trade agreement (PTA) as one of the most important documents in this due.
title: PTA, one of main documents signed by Iran, Oman recently

description: TEHRAN - Makhmoud Najafi-Arab, Head of the Tehran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines and Agriculture (TCCIMA) met with Maekawa Nobutaka, Executive Vice President of the Japan External Trade Organization (JETRO), to explore avenues for strengthening trade and economic relations between Iran and Japan, with a focus on the private sector.
title: Iranian, Japanese private sector officials discuss boosting economic ties

description: TEHRAN - Makhmoud Najafi-Arab, Head of the Tehran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines and Agriculture (TCCIMA) met with Maekawa Nobutaka, Executive Vice President of the Japan External Trade Organization (JETRO), to explore avenues for strengthening trade and economic relations between Iran and Japan, with a focus on the private sector.
title: Iranian, Japanese private sector officials discuss boosting Iran-Japan economic ties

description: TEHRAN - The 13th meeting of transport officials from member states of the Economic Cooperation Organization (ECO) kicked off on Sunday in Tehran, chaired by the Minister of Transport and Urban Development.
title: Tehran hosting 13th ECO transport ministers meeting

description: TEHRAN - Iran's nominal electricity generation capacity reached 94,649 megawatts by the end of the first months of the current Iranian calendar year (late April 2025), nearing the 95,000-megawatt threshold, according to official figures.
title: Power generation capacity nears 95,000 MW in Iran

description: TEHRAN - Iran's economy grew by three percent in the last Iranian year ending March 2025, driven primarily by gains in the industry and mining sector, according to figures published by the Statistical Center of Iran (SCI).
title: Iran's annual GDP growth reaches 3%, led by industry, mining: SCI

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s women’s hockey defeated the UAE 4-1 in the 2025 IIHF Women's Asia Cup opener Saturday night.
title: Iran start 2025 IIHF Women's Asia Cup on high

description: TEHRAN - Reigning world champions Italy ended their preparations for the Volleyball Nations League (VNL) 2025 on a high note as the Europeans swept Iran in their third and last friendly match of the season, held in Padova, on Saturday.
title: Iran fall short to Italy in VNL preperation
